Title : La Jument de Michao
Text : {{Expand French|date=April 2019}}
'''''La Jument de Michao''''' ("Michao's mare" in French) or '''''Le Loup, le Renard et la Belette''''' ("The Wolf, the Fox and the Weasel") is a recent (1973) Breton adaptation of two different Western French traditional songs, also found in Brittany, the original one may be a medieval French song of [[Burgundy]] origin: ''[[J'ai vu le loup|J'ai vu le loup, le renard, le lièvre]]''. The integration in the [[Music of Brittany|Breton patrimony]] was made under the shape of a song deduct (ten to one couplet) typical of [[Upper Brittany]] ([[Gallo language|Gallo]]), but in other French regions too. The music dances on the rhythm of the ''[[An dro]]'' ([[Vannes|Gwened]]), one of the most known [[Breton dance|Breton round dances]].

It is about a parody of liturgical ''[[Dies Irae]]'', whose origin would go back up to the fifteenth century in the country of [[Beaune]] and of which there are numerous variants in the [[French regions]].<ref>Jean Luc Tamby in ''Aux marches du palais, Romances et complaintes de la France d'autrefois'', Les chants de la terre, CD Alpha 500, Paris, 2001</ref>

==Lyrics ==
{{col-begin}}
{{col-2}}
;French
C'est dans dix ans je m'en irai<br />
J'entends le loup et le renard chanter

J'entends le loup, le renard et la belette<br />
J'entends le loup et le renard chanter

C'est dans neuf ans je m'en irai<br />
La jument de Michao a passé dans le pré

La jument de Michao et son petit poulain<br />
A passé dans le pré et mangé tout le foin

L'hiver viendra les gars, l'hiver viendra<br />
La jument de Michao, elle s'en repentira

...
{{col-2}}
;English<ref>[http://muzikum.eu/en/127-9583-104314/nolwenn-leroy/la-jument-de-michao-english-translation.html Lyrics in French and English]</ref>
In ten years, I'll go away<br />
I hear the wolf and the fox singing

I hear the wolf, the fox and the weasel<br />
I hear the wolf and the fox singing

In nine years, I'll go away<br />
Michao's mare went through the meadow

Michao's mare and its little foal<br />
Went through the meadow and ate up all the hay

Winter will come, guys, winter will come<br />
Michao's mare will regret it

...
{{col-end}}

== Records ==
* Kouerien (1973)
* [[Tri Yann]] (1976, ''La Découverte ou l'Ignorance'')
* [[Dao Dezi]] (1994)
* [[Gérard Jaffrès]] (2003, ''Viens dans ma maison'')
* [[Saltatio Mortis]] (2009, ''Wer Wind sät'') 
* [[Les Ramoneurs de Menhirs]] (2010, ''Amzer An Dispac'h'')
* [[Nolwenn Leroy]] (2010, ''[[Bretonne (album)|Bretonne]]'')
* [[Eluveitie]] (2012, ''Luxtos'', album ''Helvetios'')
* [[Laïs (band)|Laïs]] (2002, "Le renard et la belette", album "Dorothea")
* [[Omnia (band)|Omnia]] (2016, ''Wolf An Dro '', album ''Prayer'')

=== Adaptations ===
* [[Manau (group)|Manau]] (1998, ''[[Mais qui est la belette ?]]'')
* [[Gilles Servat]] (2011, ''La Manju de Chomi'', album ''Ailes et îles'')
* [[Les Enfoirés]] (2012, Le Bal des Enfoirés)

